cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.CR, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on evaluating and comparing the performance of three routing protocols in VANETs using two Mac-layer protocols. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the probability distribution function for VANETs, which can be related to information theory.
3. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The routing protocols used in VANETs involve multiple agents (vehicles) communicating with each other, which can be related to multiagent systems.
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - VANETs involve sensitive information exchange between vehicles, and security is a major concern. The paper may discuss the security aspects of the evaluated routing protocols.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The routing protocols used in VANETs involve controlling the flow of information between vehicles, which can be related to systems and control.
